    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 3200, 4100, 4200, 4300, 4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 8500, 8600
        Models Built After 05/19/2003 - HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 4100, 4200, 4300, 4400 - ADJUSTMENTS - HOOD
        STOP ADJUSTMENT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="1">
        <title>HOOD STOP ADJUSTMENT</title>
        <para>Hood height adjustment at the cowl and rear edge of hood is adjusted by moving the hood stop either up or
            down.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0900338" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900338.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 38. Hood Stop (Passenger Side Shown)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. HOOD STOP BUSHING</callout1>
                <callout1>2. HOOD STOP BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>3. FOUR (4) EACH BOLT AND WASHER</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0900338">Figure 38</hotlnk>
            for Items in parentheses.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Unlatch hood and tilt hood forward.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To adjust hood in either direction, loosen the four bolts (Item 3) located at the hood stop
                bracket.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the bracket (Item 2) upward or down to set desired height.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lower the hood and rest hood on hood stop bushings. Check rear edge alignment with cowl.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Raise the hood and re-tighten the bolts (Item 1) to secure the hood stop at the desired
                location.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The same procedure should be applied to adjust the opposite side of hood.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
